Very disappointing. Flew to New York for my birthday weekend, then took an expensive to Uber to Harlem Hookah for a reservation I made 2 weeks prior. I paid the reservation fee of $25 for one of the huts. When I arrived there was a line, I went to one of the guys in the front and told him I had a reservation. He asked to see our ID’s and sent us to the back to the line. He says he would have the manger come get us. We waited for about 20 minutes. Then a woman with dreads came out to seat people inside I guess. The woman was very nice, we told her we had a reservation and the guy sent us to the line. I could tell she was annoyed that the guy sent us to the line after telling him about the reservation. Once seated we were even more disappointed. Our waitress took our drink orders  and never came back to check on us. When we flagged her down to order food she told us they didn’t have any left. She had a bad attitude the whole night specifically toward us. Not sure why.

The Ambiance was very nice and relaxing. If you do a reservation its quick to get seated. The service is subpar for such a well known establishment. On top of me and my lady getting our food well after being seated it came out somewhat cool not HOT. If you looking for atmosphere then a great place to go but looking for anything else BEWARE!

PATHETIC. Speaking from several different experiences I've had here. Read on...***Warning this review is VERY LONG.  First Experience - my license expired (literally) the day before we came here and we were not let in. I automatically knew something was off with this place, seeing as we immediately went downtown to Babylon (our usual spot) and got in without issue.  Second Experience - Got in, and literally before we even sat down we were rudely given a list of rules- I don't remember all of them but one in particular stuck out to me - "we only accept cards that have a chip". I was confused bc for one, I thought all cards had chips on them by now- and two, as a business you should be able to accept any form of payment someone gives you from cash all the way to gift card. This is common sense. Overall from this experience, outside of being totally turned off by the list of rules, it was mediocre. The hookah wasn't as bad as I thought it would be, although it was still subpar, and the music was pretty good. They are serious about the 2 hour time limit too (one of the rules we were told about before sitting down). That's a shame bc we actually would have stayed and got another hookah, but oh well.  Third Experience - We sat at the bar on a late afternoon. Everything was OK until I realized that the water turned brown in the base. They said it was bc the oils from the pineapple were dripping down into the water. After smoking hookah at least once a week for several years I've never seen that happen before. Not at Babylon, Falucka, Zoe Cafe, Pergola, my own home- literally I have never seen that happen so clearly, something isn't right.They ended up changing out the base for us, and it turned brown again. At this point we were over it and just wrapped up. I guess they tried.  Fourth Experience - The base turned brown again. We complained again and they said the same thing. The manager gave us a new one- and I expected the water to turn brown again, but surprisingly it didn't. What was done different I wonder? Still very weak on the flavoring. Despite that this experience wasn't horrible.  Fifth AND FINAL Experience - Came yesterday evening 12/15/18 around 7pm and (like all the other reviewers) waited outside for someone to come and seat us only to walk into a damn near empty place- it's only two of us so it's not like we would have taken up a lot of space just standing inside. Laughable. The hookah again was not great but we were still going to vibe. We preferred to sit at the bar, so when we saw some seats open up we moved over there. I go to the bathroom real quick and come back to a combative, pathetic excuse for an entry level "manager" aggressively moving my stuff back over to the table. What he was trying to say was "I'm sorry guys, we have some people waiting outside for these seats so we'll need you to move back to the table"- or he could have sat them at the table??? Instead he came over questioning my fiancee- "who told you to come over here?"(bar seating is always first come first serve) "Did you even close out at the table?" (the waiter can very easily close our bill while we're sitting right here)"We can do this the easy way or the hard way" - EXCUSE ME?! NOPE, NOPE, NOPE - BRING US THE BILL. We absolutely will not tolerate hood rat behavior from any so called "manager on duty". YOU ARE TRASH.  The fact is that we live so close to HH so we've given it several tries. After that last exchange with that miserable "manager" that really put the nail in the coffin. I hate that this place is the way that it is. There are so many little changes that can be made to make this place somewhat desirable. Stop reading off a bunch of rules, making people wait outside for literally no reason, having rude staff, having malfunctioning hookah's - to name a few. We never have these sorts of problems at any other hookah place we go to, so that's where we will continue to spend our money. I advise other's to do the same. At least we gave it a few good tries.

this was my review that was from Resy but, the site won’t let you post the review no matter what length so, i took my talents to yelp and google 🙂  what went wrong you ask? well, let’s see...made a reservation for a party of four, at 6:30pm on a Sunday. At a normal establishment, you’d think that this would mean you’d be getting seasted shortly or AT THE LEAST, allowed inside to wait because it’s only damn near winter outside. Nope, not here. Instead you wait outside while the hostess dances around, texting on her phone, chatting it up with all of everyone inside. Not to mention, it was dead in there. So there’s actually no reason why the hostess was so very “booked and busy”.  By now, frustrated as hell, we ask the bouncer what the hold up was and even he was saying how disrespectful what was happening was. By now the time is 6:36pm, asked to speak with a manager, takes him an additional several minutes to come out and I explained the situation and then the hostess comes out, says nothing to us...STILL all while the manager is being very combative with me telling me “we don’t seat guest before their reservation time” meanwhile it is now after our said reservation time and yet still, no one even bothered to come outside to tell us anything in regards to anything. Long story long, we did not end up staying. When this place first opened service was phenomal. As time went by, service has declined IMMENSELY. You want to try so hard to support local black businesses but it’s truly hard when they do not value their customers with respect and exude the worst attitudes possible. Please do not waste your time coming here unless, you could care less about being treated the way many of the reviews say this establishment treats their customers.

Customer service improvement needed. Brought some friends from out of town to come enjoy the vibe and mood Sunday night. There were 5 us, looking to get a table, the place was full but not packed.  The line at the door is just ridiculous for a place that isn’t packed — but were frustrated to hear that to get a table, there is a 4:1 hookah policy and the 5 of us would have to get 2 hookahs.  I explained, as an asthmatic person that doesn’t smoke — the extra hookah wouldn’t be necessary. The hostess explained the “house” policy, and again I explained that I don’t smoke. Totally getting the policy and willing to spend an adequate amount to supplement the decision not to get second hookah, we made eye contact and the hostess then explained that the bar was available and we could sit and get one hookah. Not wanting to escalate situation and still wanting to treat my out of town guests well, we buckled and accepted the seats at the bar.  Generally house policies are understood, management should consider alternatives and appropriate accommodations for patrons that aren’t able to comply for health reasons.

Before entering I was greeted by a bouncer who demanded to know the name on the reservation. It was raining outside, I asked if I could get passed the black rope to get some coverage from the rain. The bouncer declined and had me wait outside until H confirmed my reservation. The place is beautifully decored. We ran a little late and had to wait at the bar. The bartender was very active and always checking in. We weren’t seat until almost 1 hr and 30 mins. The hostess kept lying about the wait time and even made up a story about us making reservations for a bigger size party, claiming we had to wait for everyone to be there; but we only reserved for 2. We had to close out at the bar before we were seated. After ordering our meal we had to ASK for basics like water, utensils and napkins. Everytime we wanted service we had to consistently and actively work to gain our waitress attention. The experience was a real nightmare. It’s unfortunate being so that the place has so much potential. They really lack tentative customer service. The drinks and food was good though.
